[[File:Adalar 5540.jpg|thumb|Büyükada quay, [[Prince Islands]],[[Sea of Marmara]] ]] [[File:Anadolu Kavağı.jpg|thumb|Anadolukavağı quay, [[Bosphorus]], [[Anatolia]]n side. ]] [[File:Bostancı pier.jpg|thumb|Bostancı quay, [[Sea of Marmara]]. ]] [[File:KadıköyOldFerryPier (1).jpg|thumb|Kadıköy old quay, [[Sea of Marmara]]. ]] [[File:Jetty in Kanlıca on the Bosphorus, Turkey 001.JPG|thumb|Kanlıca quay, [[Bosphorus]], [[Anatolia]]n side]] [[File:Sütlüce İskelesi - panoramio.jpg|thumb|Sütlüce quay, [[Golden Horn]], east side. ]]
There are 50 passenger '''ferry quays in İstanbul''', of which 37 are in active service in [[Bosphorus]], [[Golden Horn]] and the [[Sea of Marmara]].<ref name="sh1"/> As of the 2017 Summer season, the ferry quays are served at 600 voyages daily by 28 traditional passenger ferry boats on 17 lines operated by the ''Şehir Hatları'' ("City Lines") company.<ref name="sh2"/>
Following is the list of active ferry quays:
