The '''Padina Plateau''' is high-altitude region in the [[Bucegi Mountains]] situated at 1500m above sea level. Among the plateau's attractions is the Bolboci Lake. Also on the plateau is the Padina National Mountain Rescue Centre.<ref name="montania">{{cite web|url=http://www.montania.ro/en_Sinaia_S.htm|publisher=montania.ro|title=Sinaia summer Hiking routes in Bucegi Mountains, rock climbing, mountain bike in Bucegi|accessdate=2017-02-25}}</ref> Nearby is the [[Babele]] area of rock formation and the Omu Peak (2505m), the 11th highest point in Romania.

