The '''Panama Plate''' is a small [[tectonic plate]] sandwiched between the [[Cocos Plate]] and [[Nazca Plate]] to the south and the [[Caribbean Plate]] to the north. Most of its borders are [[convergent boundary|convergent boundarie]]s including a [[subduction zone]] to the west. It consists, for the most part, of the nations of [[Panama]] and [[Costa Rica]].

