{{Infobox mountain | name = Wharite Peak | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 920 | elevation_ref = | prominence = | map = New Zealand | map_caption = | map_size = | coordinates = {{coord|40.25465|S|175.85837|E|type:mountain_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Manawatu-Wanganui]], New Zealand | range = [[Ruahine Range]] | type = | age = | volcanic_arc/belt = | last_eruption = | first_ascent = }} '''Wharite Peak''' is a mountain at the southern end of the [[Ruahine Range]], {{convert|9|km|abbr=on}} north of [[Woodville, New Zealand|Woodville]] in the [[Manawatu-Wanganui]] region of New Zealand. The mountain is home to the main television transmitter for the city of [[Palmerston North]] and the wider Manawatu region.
==Transmitter== A 1&nbsp;kW television transmitter was established atop Wharite in 1963, relaying [[TVNZ 1|WNTV1]] from Wellington. It was replaced with a 100&nbsp;kW transmitter in 1966.<ref>{{cite journal |title= Parliamentary Debates (Hansard) |publisher= New Zealand Parliament |volume=351 |page=1394 |date= 28 June 1967 }}</ref>
